Package main

Class AVLPlayerNode

java.lang.Object
main.AVLPlayerNode
public class AVLPlayerNode extends Object
AVLPlayerNode class for the nodes of the AVL tree Each node will have a left child, a right child, and a Player object, a double (the value that the node is sorted based on), balance factor for AVL balancing, number of nodes in the right subtree.

  • Method Details

    • insert

      public AVLPlayerNode insert(Player newGuy, double value)
      Inserts a new player node with the specified player data and numerical value into the AVL tree. Self-balancing insert method.
      Parameters:
      newGuy - the player data to be inserted into the tree
      value - value associated with the new player node
      Returns:
      the new root of the AVL tree after insertion O(h) run time where h represents the height of the tree. Average case of O(log n).

    • delete

      public AVLPlayerNode delete(double value)
      Deletes a player node with the specified numerical value The right weight is updated, and the new root of the tree is returned.
      Parameters:
      value - the numerical value associated with the player node to be deleted
      Returns:
      the new root of the AVL tree after deletion O(h) run time - h is height of the tree

    • rotateRight

      public void rotateRight()
      Rotates the AVL tree to the right around this node The rightWeight is updated. O(h) run time - h is the height of the tree. Average case is O(log n) for a balanced tree

    • rotateLeft

      public void rotateLeft()
      Rotates the AVL tree to the left around this node. The rightWeight is updated. O(h) run time - h is the height of the tree. Average case is O(log n) for a balanced tree

    • getRank

      public int getRank(double value)
      Retrieves the rank of the node with the specified numerical value in the AVL tree. The rank represents the number of nodes in the tree with values less than or equal to the specified value.
      Parameters:
      value - value associated with the player node
      Returns:
      the rank of the node with the specified value in the AVL tree
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the specified value is not found in the AVL tree O(h) run time - h is the height of the tree. Average case is O(log n) for a balanced tree
